Slit chunks of lamb and insert garlic slivers, set aside. In a heavy-bottom casserole, heat oil over medium heat. Add onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly caramelized, 10 to 12 minutes. Add lamb and brown on all sides. Add stock, coriander and bay leaves. Cover and decrease heat to medium-low. Cook until tender, about 1Â½ hours. Discard bay leaves. Set lamb aside. Combine lentils and broth. Cover and cook until lentils are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Return lamb to pot and season with salt and pepper. Heat through. Add vinegar or wine before serving, Garnish with fresh coriander.